  <summary date="2017-03-09T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Future Logging Careers Act 

This bill amends the Fair Labor Standards Act of 1938 to make the restrictions on oppressive child labor inapplicable to employment of an employee age 16 or 17 by a parent, or a person standing in place of a parent, in a logging or mechanized operation owned or operated by that parent or person.</summary>
